==Herblore==
* '''Otto Godblessed:''' Good day to you, hearty warrior! May the spirits guide you.
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|Tell me more about the use of spears.}}
* {{topt|What was that secret knowledge of herblore we talked of?}}
** '''Player:''' What was that secret knowledge of herblore we talked of?
** '''Otto Godblessed:''' The secret is linked to the fish in the lake nearby. If you use your knife upon them, several new fishy items will be produced. Fish parts can be used as bait, but the roe and caviar is more useful for us.
** '''Player:''' Do I cook them?
** '''Otto Godblessed:''' Certainly not. Mixing these items with two dose potions is what should be done. This results in a nutritious slop, perfect for healing as well as imparting the effect of the potion.
** '''Otto Godblessed:''' Roe can only be used for some of the more easily combined mixes, while caviar may be used for any of the mixes of which I am aware.
** '''Player:''' What if I only have four dose potions?
** '''Otto Godblessed:''' You are able to decant a four dose potion into an empty vial, thus giving two potions of two doses. This will aid you in the process.
** '''Player:''' I guess you just want me to go away and make one of these potions?
** '''Otto Godblessed:''' Have I become so predictable? But yes, I do indeed require a potion. It is of the highest importance that you bring me a lesser attack potion combined with fish roe.
